sql:
SELECT lithology_description, lithology_codes, rock_type, COUNT(*) as rock_type_count
FROM lithology
GROUP BY rock_type;

SELECT section_name, bottom_interval_depth
FROM sections
WHERE bottom_interval_depth = (SELECT MIN(bottom_interval_depth) FROM sections);

SELECT expedition_name
FROM expeditions
WHERE start_date > '2022-01-01';

SELECT lithology_description
FROM lithology
WHERE rock_type = 'Sedimentary';

SELECT COUNT(*) 
FROM lithology 
WHERE rock_type = 'Sedimentary';

external_knowledge:
Top 3 refers to the highest rank based on the total number of cores per expedition; 
expedition can be understood as a collection of cores; 
cores can be understood as the basic units of data collection in this context.

sql:
SELECT hardness_description, hardness_type
FROM hardness_induration
WHERE hardness_codes = 'SOF';

SELECT structure_description
FROM structures
WHERE structure_id = (SELECT MIN(structure_id) FROM structures);

external_knowledge:
The 'top 3 sections' refers to the sections with the smallest top interval depths, indicating they are closest to the surface; 
In the context of geological expeditions, 'sections' refer to the segments of a core sample that have been analyzed; 
The 'lithology, deformation, and paleontology details' provide information about the composition, structural changes, and fossil records of the sections, respectively.
